WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.160
Let's be real. AI is here. It's in our
schools, and students are already using

00:00:04.160 --> 00:00:07.880
it. This tool is a game changer. It helps
with ideas,

00:00:07.900 --> 00:00:11.420
or it'll write the whole paper for you. So
what is it?

00:00:11.540 --> 00:00:14.100
A brilliant helper or the ultimate
cheating machine?

00:00:14.440 --> 00:00:18.680
Let's dive in. Okay, the number one fear
with AI in school?

00:00:19.040 --> 00:00:22.160
Cheating. Plain and simple. And students
are caught in the middle.

00:00:22.380 --> 00:00:24.920
They use it for ideas, but are scared to
get busted.

00:00:25.260 --> 00:00:30.080
And get this, more than half of students
say they'd use AI even if it's banned.

00:00:30.420 --> 00:00:34.640
So this has kicked off a kind of arms
race. Schools are buying AI police to

00:00:34.640 --> 00:00:38.860
catch it. But you gotta wonder, how good
are these AI detectors really?

00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:42.320
Well, studies show their accuracy is all
over the map.

00:00:42.420 --> 00:00:46.700
It's basically a guessing game. And that
means essays written by humans can get

00:00:46.700 --> 00:00:51.540
flagged as AI. A huge problem. And it gets
worse. Beyond just

00:00:51.540 --> 00:00:54.620
being wrong, there's a much bigger
problem. Fairness.

00:00:55.120 --> 00:00:59.660
See, these AI systems learn from the
internet, which can lead to some really

00:00:59.660 --> 00:01:03.340
unfair results. This means certain
students get flagged more often,

00:01:03.500 --> 00:01:06.980
even when they did the work themselves.
Okay, so if the AI police don't work,

00:01:07.080 --> 00:01:11.120
what's the real answer here? Well, one
idea is to change the assignments,

00:01:11.340 --> 00:01:15.120
making them way harder to cheat on with
AI. Instead of just banning it,

00:01:15.300 --> 00:01:17.600
a lot of teachers want to teach kids how
to use it right.

00:01:18.060 --> 00:01:22.360
Some schools are using guides just like
this one to show when and how AI is okay

00:01:22.360 --> 00:01:27.060
to use. The key is to use AI like a tool,
not as a replacement

00:01:27.060 --> 00:01:31.120
for actually thinking. A good way to think
about it is human AI human.

00:01:31.440 --> 00:01:36.080
You start, AI helps, you finish. This way,
AI becomes a

00:01:36.080 --> 00:01:40.760
co-pilot for learning, not the actual
pilot. So the tool is here to

00:01:40.760 --> 00:01:43.920
stay. The real question is, how are we
going to choose to use it?